label: intense
definition: Intense alteration refers to an almost complete to complete replacement of the primary minerals and obliteration of original textures.

label: moderate
definition: Moderate intensity indicates alteration in which several of the primary mineral species have been replaced, with some modification of the original textures.

label: strong
definition: Strong intensity indicates alteration in which the majority of the primary minerals have been replaced, with considerable modification of the original textures.

label: unaltered
definition: A rock with no visible signs of alteration, in which primary minerals, fabrics (including primary pore space) and chemistry are unchanged.

label: weak
definition: Weak, or low, intensity indicates alteration in which only a few of the primary mineral species have been replaced, with little or no modification of the original textures.
